commit.message:
Fix warnings about single quotes in docstrings

This commit fixes "docstring has wrong usage of unescaped single quotes"
warnings. Closes #507.

Change `(setf (point) ...)` and similar forms to `(goto-char ...)`

Emacs version 29.0.50 has deprecated the use of forms such as
`(setf (point) n)`. The warning emitted is: -

Warning (bytecomp): ‘point’ is an obsolete generalized variable; use
‘goto-char’ instead.
Update example link

Ensure elfeed-search-browse-url stays in Elfeed buffer

If some emacs internal browser such as `eww` is invoked by `browse-url`,
the remainder of the function ran in the `eww` buffer which didn't make
sense and didn't visually mark the entry as read.

Fixes #425. Closes #426.

Set risky-local-variable on header line symbol

This allows header line strings to be propertized as before, correcting
the fix for #415.
Fix up a couple dependencies in the Makefile

Fix %-construct handling in search header line

This string was never intended to be interpolated, and the documentation
for header-line-format is not obvious that it would be. Rather than try
to escape %-constructs with a regexp, disable interpolation completely
by providing the string indirectly via a symbol's value slot.

Fixes #415.
Fix up Makefile dependency tracking
Add missing require to elfeed-curl-tests.el
Bump to 3.4.1
Fix comment and last-entry behaviour

commit.message: Bump to 3.4.0

Comprehensive elfeed-curl-get-capabilities results

Rather than a boolean for every this and that, return full lists of
supported protocols and features.

elfeed-curl: Add gopher protocol support

Fixes issue #408 and closes PR #410

Lack of cURL gopher support (on a sufficiently older version of cURL or
using the built-in `url-retrieve' functionality in Emacs) will result in
error messages about unsupported messages in the logs.
No longer query users about running curl processes

Add support for local feeds

Fixes #300, closes #397.

Fix up elfeed-show-next/prev

These functions expected #'elfeed-search-show-entry would move forward one
line. However, when elfeed-search-remain-on-entry is set to t, it won't, so we
need to do it manually.
Add README link to elfeed-dashboard

Don't cache the search buffer header

Basing it on the modified tick count is definitely wrong, and we don't
really need the cache anyway.

Remove "End of entries" from elfeed-search

This never really served much purpose, and it interferes with selecting
things, so get rid of it. We must manually force a header line update,
though, if the buffer did not change at all (i.e. it started empty and
ended empty).
Add README article link about Bongo

Fix up date filter tests

Due to a bug in Emacs 25 (all releases) where ERT tests don't expand
macros properly, these tests didn't actually work. However, we don't
actually need or want a macro here anyway, so just get rid of it!

Eliminate some obsolete function warnings

If the new function is present, use it, otherwise use the old function
but explicitly disable the warning. Elfeed still supports back to Emacs
24.3 where these newer functions don't exist.

Refactor: leverage cl-destructuring-bind

Simplify series of `plist-get' assignments with `cl-destructuring-bind'.
Add README article link about viewing videos
Add three README links to recent Elfeed articles
Add two recent Elfeed articles to README

Add defcustoms for elfeed-show-entry- functions

Fixes #361.

Add support for bookmarks in entries

Closes #358

Properly integrate elfeed-search-tests (#356)

These tests were never being run, nor did they even work in the first
place.
